						<summary>

						<p>On a slab built into the wall of the Chennakēśavasvāmi temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated 1[609], Akshaya, Vaiśākha śu. 15.</p>						

						<p>Records that Narabālapāṭi Rāmachandraya, son of Peda-Chennamarāju, who was a devotee of the god Gōpālasvāmi of Narabālapāḍu offered salutations to the god Lakshmīnarasiṁha.</p>						

